value.0: An old man garbed in the black and white robes of Kelemvor's clergy and bearing the seal of the Office of Illumination.

Despite the voluminous black robe of this Kelemvorite, it is mortifyingly obvious that he is a leper.  Shadowed, but still noticeable, a stump remains from the amputation of his left hand, and three decrepit fingers remain on his right.  As he fixes his gaze upon you, tilting his head to one angle to view you with his remaining good eye, the dim light of the smoky room reveals a nightmarish face-- one eye is pale and clouded over, and all that is left of his nose is a skull-like stump.  His lips are red and white with the disease, crackled and hopelessly disfigured.

This fellow has obviously seen many a day and night in service to the Eternal Order.  He stands like an ageless guardian, resolute and quiet in his black and white uniform and templar's helm.  The sun has bleached his tunic, and grains of sand have lodged themselves into the links of his chainmail, and yet he continues to stand firm.  His demeanor is grim, his aura that of one tried and true, and his hand often reaches down to touch the symbol of Kelemvor hanging at his belt, as if offering an unconscious prayer to his lord.

This finely crafted and blessed helmet is a part of the uniform of the Ravensword Regimet of the Eternal Order that is now stationed in the deserts of Khem. Under the left eye slit of the helmet the scales of justice upheld by a skeletal arm can be seen, the symbol of the Judge of the Dead.

These helmets were blessed by the priests of the Bastion of Sankt Elizabeth to grant the owner the strength and the consitution needed to do his or her duty in these lands.

This is one of the sacred full plates that have been crafted and blessed for the members of the Eternal Order of Lord Kelemvor. The ancient words of prayer carved into the armor are the source of its protective magic.

Due to the extreme heat in Khem these uniforms are seldom used, as the way they have been built may protect from the most devastating blows, but will bring the wearer down due to extreme exhaustion as they offer no protection from the sun.
Inquisitorial Acolyte of Order of Saint Elizabeth

A beautiful paladin with ash-blonde shoulder-length hair, fair skin and soft brown eyes stands before you. She wears the armor of a Knight-Templar, with its red-trimmed tabard and raven crest embroidered in threads of silver rather than the black of the other Order knights. Holy symbols adorn her tabard and seals inscribed with sacred texts are proudly displayed like military ribbons and honors. Her expression is calm but unmistakably determined.

A man in his forties with long dirty blond hair and a short unkempt beard. He looks a bit more relaxed than the other clergy here, and smiles pleasantly as you approach. He smells rather strongly of garlic!

- Do not take the tomes out of the library.

- Return the tomes to their rightful place after using them.

- Conduct yourself in a manner fitting this sanctuary of knowlege.

- Do not bring food or drink into the library, this is a place of parchment and ink.

- The tomes inside this library may be copied, however this must be overseen by the librarian to ensure that these rarities are not damaged in the process.
There is nothing special about this object.

This prisoner whimpers and screams in his sleep, his will nothing more than shattered remains of its former glory after the Inquisitors were done with him. He often calls out for forgivness as his the faces of those he wronged come back to haunt him.
The torch paints its environs in warmer hues. You find yourself grateful for its glow.

We are the the Eternal Order, the right hand of Lord Kelemvor, the instrument of His will, the gauntlet about His fist, the edge of His sword!

We are His most devoted servants, armoured in Faith, shielded by Devotion and armed with Purity of Purpose.

But greater even than these, we carry His light into the pits of heresy, to purge it wherever it may be found!
